---
const bathPoints = [
  {
    head: "Power, dialed to the dog",
    body: "A lever at the nozzle sets the water from a soft trickle to full force. Full force drives water through a thick double coat to the skin. Soft is right for a face, eyes, and nervous dogs. Powerful does not have to mean rough.",
  },
  {
    head: "Finishes on clean water",
    body: "The wash recirculates and gets your dog clean the way a dishwasher does. Every dog finishes with a fresh water rinse from a separate tank.",
  },
  {
    head: "No dog too dirty",
    body: "Mud from nose to tail is a normal day. When the wash water turns to a puddle, we flush, refill, and wash again until your dog washes up clean.",
  },
  {
    head: "Easy on water",
    body: "Most dogs are washed and rinsed with under five gallons. The power comes from how the system moves water, not from wasting it.",
  },
];

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is it gentle?",
    a: "Yes. The pressure dials down to a soft trickle, so faces, eyes, and small or nervous dogs get a soft bath.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is my dog washed in clean water?",
    a: "The wash recirculates and gets your dog clean the way a dishwasher does. An extra-dirty dog is flushed and washed again with fresh water, and every dog finishes on a clean-water rinse from a separate tank.",
  },
  {
    q: "What shampoo do you use?",
    a: "A gentle shampoo and conditioner that suits nearly every dog. If your dog needs something specific, medicated, or for a particular condition, bring it and we will use it.",
  },
  {
    q: "How dirty is too dirty?",
    a: "Just about nothing. Mud from nose to tail is a normal day.",
  },
];

---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Dog Gone Clean | Mobile dog baths in The Villages, Florida</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Dog Gone Clean is a mobile dog bath service in The Villages, Florida, powered by the Hurricane Bath. A genuinely clean dog in your driveway, on a schedule you keep."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="glow glow-a"></div>
    <div class="glow glow-b"></div>

    <header class="site">
      <img class="brand-logo" src="/logo.png" alt="Dog Gone Clean" />
      <a class="portal" href="/portal/">Client sign in</a>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <p class="eyebrow">Mobile dog baths in The Villages, Florida</p>
        <h1>A bath your dog<br /><span class="grad">actually likes.</span></h1>
        <p class="lede">
          Powered by the Hurricane Bath, in your driveway, by the same familiar
          face every visit. A genuinely clean dog, calmly handled, without the
          trip.
        </p>
        <div class="cta">
          <a class="button primary" href="/portal/">Book a visit</a>
          <a class="button ghost" href="#bath">Meet the Hurricane Bath</a>
        </div>
        <p class="trio">Structured. Reliable. Personal.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="why">
        <p class="eyebrow">Why Paul built it</p>
        <h2>None of the systems he could buy did everything he wanted in one machine.</h2>
        <p>
          So he built the one that does. Years of working with the professional
          systems showed him what to keep and what was missing, and he put all of
          it into a single machine tuned exactly the way he wants to wash a dog.
          There is nothing else quite like it, and he is still refining it.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="bath" class="bath">
        <p class="eyebrow light">The Hurricane Bath</p>
        <h2>A serious bath, <span class="grad">at your door.</span></h2>
        <p class="lede">
          The Hurricane Bath moves up to about ten gallons a minute, the kind of
          flow you get from city water, and dials all the way down to a soft
          trickle for a dog's face and eyes. Paul built it himself, and it gets a
          dog genuinely clean, fast.
        </p>
        <div class="grid">
          {
            bathPoints.map((p) => (
              <article class="card dark">
                <h3>{p.head}</h3>
                <p>{p.body}</p>
              </article>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="faq">
        <p class="eyebrow">Questions, answered</p>
        <h2>Honest answers about the Hurricane Bath.</h2>
        <div class="qa-list">
          {
            faqs.map((f) => (
              <article class="qa">
                <h3>{f.q}</h3>
                <p>{f.a}</p>
              </article>
            ))
          }
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="power">
        <h2>Power to spare, <span class="grad">quiet by choice.</span></h2>
        <p>
          The two generators are inverter models, chosen to run at about the
          volume of a normal conversation. Paul paid more for them so your
          visit stays peaceful.
        </p>
        <p>
          That power runs the air conditioning, the dehumidifier, and the
          high-velocity dryers, so your dog is comfortable the whole time
          and dry quickly.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="arrival">
        <p class="eyebrow">Now in The Villages, Florida</p>
        <h2>The trailer parks in your driveway.<br />The bath happens.<br /><span class="grad">Your dog walks back inside, clean.</span></h2>
        <p>
          That is the whole visit. You stay home. Your dog gets focused care.
          The trailer carries its own water, power, and climate control, so
          nothing about your day has to change. Just your dog, the Hurricane
          Bath, and one familiar face.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="about">
        <h2>Meet Paul Nickerson</h2>
        <p>
          Paul did not fall into this business by accident. He chose dogs. He
          wanted to build his life around working with them, so he trained at the
          Florida Institute of Animal Arts and built Dog Gone Clean from the
          ground up in Ocala, Florida.
        </p>
        <p>
          What started as one trailer and one decision became a focused mobile
          dog grooming service built on calm handling and full attention. The
          system came later. The dogs came first.
        </p>
        <p class="sign">Paul Nickerson, Owner, Dog Gone Clean</p>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <span>Dog Gone Clean</span>
      <span>Mobile dog baths, The Villages FL</span>
    </footer>

    <style>
      :root {
        --ink: #0c1322;
        --muted: #5a6b7d;
        --bg: #f7f9ff;
        --card: #ffffff;
        --accent: #2563eb;
        --accent2: #06b6d4;
        --line: #e3e8f4;
      }
      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }
      html {
        scroll-behavior: smooth;
      }
      body {
        margin: 0;
        position: relative;
        overflow-x: hidden;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
        color: var(--ink);
        background: var(--bg);
        line-height: 1.55;
      }
      .glow {
        position: absolute;
        z-index: 0;
        border-radius: 50%;
        filter: blur(90px);
        opacity: 0.5;
        pointer-events: none;
      }
      .glow-a {
        top: -120px;
        right: -80px;
        width: 420px;
        height: 420px;
        background: radial-gradient(circle, #3b82f6, transparent 70%);
      }
      .glow-b {
        top: 600px;
        left: -120px;
        width: 380px;
        height: 380px;
        background: radial-gradient(circle, #22d3ee, transparent 70%);
      }
      .site,
      main,
      .site-footer {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
      }
      .site {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 1.1rem 1.4rem;
        max-width: 980px;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }
      .brand-logo {
        height: 108px;
        width: auto;
        display: block;
      }
      @media (max-width: 480px) {
        .brand-logo {
          height: 80px;
        }
      }
      .portal {
        color: var(--accent);
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 600;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
      }
      main {
        max-width: 980px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.4rem;
      }
      .eyebrow {
        text-transform: uppercase;
        letter-spacing: 0.09em;
        font-size: 0.8rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--accent);
        margin: 0 0 0.7rem;
      }
      .eyebrow.light {
        color: var(--accent2);
      }
      .hero {
        padding: 3rem 0 3.5rem;
      }
      h1 {
        font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 9vw, 4.6rem);
        line-height: 1.02;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
        font-weight: 800;
      }
      .grad {
        background: linear-gradient(100deg, var(--accent), var(--accent2));
        -webkit-background-clip: text;
        background-clip: text;
        color: transparent;
      }
      .lede {
        font-size: 1.18rem;
        color: #41506a;
        max-width: 36rem;
        margin: 0 0 1.7rem;
      }
      .cta {
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.8rem;
      }
      .button {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 0.85rem 1.4rem;
        border-radius: 999px;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 700;
      }
      .primary {
        background: linear-gradient(100deg, var(--accent), var(--accent2));
        color: #fff;
        box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(37, 99, 235, 0.35);
      }
      .ghost {
        background: #fff;
        color: var(--ink);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
      .trio {
        margin: 1.8rem 0 0;
        font-weight: 700;
        letter-spacing: 0.04em;
        color: #41506a;
      }
      section h2 {
        font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.2rem);
        letter-spacing: -0.01em;
        margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
        font-weight: 800;
      }
      .services,
      .power,
      .arrival,
      .about,
      .why,
      .faq {
        padding: 1.8rem 0 2.6rem;
      }
      .arrival h2 {
        line-height: 1.15;
        max-width: 30rem;
      }
      .arrival p {
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        color: #41506a;
        max-width: 40rem;
      }
      .why h2 {
        max-width: 40rem;
        line-height: 1.18;
      }
      .why p {
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        color: #41506a;
        max-width: 44rem;
        margin: 0;
      }
      .faq h2 {
        max-width: 40rem;
      }
      .qa-list {
        display: grid;
        gap: 0.9rem;
        max-width: 46rem;
      }
      .qa {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 14px;
        padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem;
        box-shadow: 0 4px 14px rgba(13, 30, 70, 0.04);
      }
      .qa h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
        font-size: 1.05rem;
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      .qa p {
        margin: 0;
        color: #41506a;
      }
      .grid {
        display: grid;
        gap: 1rem;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(230px, 1fr));
      }
      .card {
        background: var(--card);
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 16px;
        padding: 1.4rem;
        box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(13, 30, 70, 0.05);
      }
      .card h3 {
        margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
        color: var(--accent);
      }
      .card p {
        margin: 0;
        color: #41506a;
      }
      .bath {
        position: relative;
        margin: 1rem -1.4rem;
        padding: 3rem 1.4rem;
        color: #eaf2ff;
        background: linear-gradient(160deg, #0c1322, #15233f 60%, #0e2a3a);
        border-radius: 24px;
      }
      .bath h2 {
        color: #fff;
      }
      .bath .lede {
        color: #b9cae8;
      }
      .card.dark {
        background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
        border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
        box-shadow: none;
      }
      .card.dark h3 {
        color: #67e8f9;
      }
      .card.dark p {
        color: #b9cae8;
      }
      .power p,
      .about p {
        font-size: 1.08rem;
        color: #41506a;
        max-width: 44rem;
        margin: 0 0 1rem;
      }
      .chips {
        list-style: none;
        padding: 0;
        margin: 1rem 0 0;
        display: flex;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.6rem;
      }
      .chips li {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        border-radius: 999px;
        padding: 0.45rem 1rem;
        font-size: 0.95rem;
        font-weight: 600;
      }
      .about .sign {
        font-weight: 700;
        color: var(--ink);
      }
      .site-footer {
        max-width: 980px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 2.5rem 1.4rem 3.5rem;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        flex-wrap: wrap;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        color: #5a6b7d;
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
